## Источники

### DSM-5 и классификация
- APA. Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, 5th ed., Text Revision (DSM-5-TR). 2022.
- APA. DSM-5-TR Fact Sheets: Bipolar I and Bipolar II Disorders. 2022.

### Эпидемиология
- Merikangas KR et al. Prevalence and correlates of bipolar spectrum disorder in the World Mental Health Survey Initiative. Arch Gen Psychiatry 2011; 68: 241–251.
- Kessler RC et al. (NCS-R). National Comorbidity Survey Replication.
- Bellivier F et al. Admixture analysis of age at onset in bipolar I. Arch Gen Psychiatry 2003.

### Продольное течение
- Judd LL, Akiskal HS, Schettler PJ et al. The long-term natural history of the weekly symptomatic status of bipolar I disorder. Arch Gen Psychiatry 2002; 59: 530–537.
- Judd LL, Akiskal HS. Depressive episodes and symptoms dominate the longitudinal course of bipolar disorder. 2003.
- Post RM et al. Morbidity in 258 bipolar outpatients followed for 1 year (Stanley Foundation Bipolar Network). J Clin Psychiatry 2003; 64: 680–690.
- Joffe RT et al. A prospective, longitudinal study of percentage of time spent ill in patients with bipolar I or bipolar II disorders. Bipolar Disord 2004; 6: 62–66.
- Coryell W, Keller M, Endicott J. Bipolar II illness: course and outcome over a five-year period. Psychol Med 1989.

### Misdiagnosis
- Hirschfeld RM et al. NDMDA Survey: misdiagnosis of bipolar disorder. J Clin Psychiatry 2003.
- Altamura AC et al. Misdiagnosis, duration of untreated illness (DUI) and outcome in bipolar patients with psychotic symptoms. J Affect Disord 2015.
- Singh T, Rajput M. Misdiagnosis of bipolar disorder. Psychiatry (Edgmont) 2006; 3(10): 57–63.

### Kindling и модели
- Post RM. Transduction of psychosocial stress into the neurobiology of recurrent affective disorder. Am J Psychiatry 1992; 149: 999–1010.
- Post RM. Kindling and sensitization as models for affective episode recurrence. Neurosci Biobehav Rev 2007.
- Bender RE, Alloy LB. Life stress and kindling in bipolar disorder: review of the evidence. Clin Psychol Rev 2011; 31: 383–398.
- Kessing LV et al. The predictive effect of episodes on the risk of recurrence. Acta Psychiatr Scand 2004.
- Goodwin FK, Jamison KR. Manic-Depressive Illness: Bipolar Disorders and Recurrent Depression. 2nd ed. Oxford University Press, 2007.

### Суицид
- Schaffer A et al. International Society for Bipolar Disorders Task Force on Suicide. Bipolar Disord 2015.
- Rihmer Z. Suicide and bipolar disorder. In: Bipolar Depression. Springer, 2007.
- Baldessarini RJ et al. Lithium treatment and suicide risk in major affective disorders. J Clin Psychiatry 2006.

### Когнитивные нарушения
- Martinez-Aran A et al. Cognitive function across manic or hypomanic, depressed, and euthymic states in bipolar disorder. Am J Psychiatry 2004.
- Bora E et al. Cognitive deficits in bipolar disorder: a meta-analysis. J Affect Disord 2009.

### Лечение
- Yatham LN et al. CANMAT and ISBD 2018 guidelines for the management of patients with bipolar disorder. Bipolar Disord 2018; 20: 97–170.
- Yatham LN et al. CANMAT and ISBD Guidelines: Summary and a 2023 Update. Bipolar Disord 2024.
- NICE Clinical Guideline CG185: Bipolar disorder: assessment and management. 2014 (updated 2023).
- Goodwin GM et al. BAP 2016 guidelines for treatment of bipolar disorder. J Psychopharmacol 2016.

### Функционирование
- Altshuler LL et al. Subsyndromal depressive symptoms are associated with functional impairment in patients with bipolar disorder. J Clin Psychiatry 2006; 67: 1551–1560.
- Judd LL et al. Psychosocial disability and work role function compared across the long-term course of bipolar I, bipolar II, and unipolar major depressive disorders. J Affect Disord 2005; 73: 19–32.

### Спектральная модель
- Akiskal HS. The prevalent clinical spectrum of bipolar disorders. J Clin Psychopharmacol 1996.
- Akiskal HS, Benazzi F. The DSM-IV and ICD-10 categories of recurrent depression vs bipolar II. J Affect Disord 2005.

### Обзорные работы
- Vieta E et al. Bipolar disorders: an update on critical aspects. Lancet Regional Health Europe 2024.
- Grande I et al. Bipolar disorder. Lancet 2016; 387: 1561–1572.

